Alstom, Deutsche Boerse, Exmar, Korian: European Equity Preview

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   A .   J o h n s o n
-- 
2011-03-24T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/alstom-deutsche-boerse-exmar-korian-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index advanced 0.5 percent to 273.11.
The Stoxx 50 Index slumped 0.6 percent to 2,566.07. The Euro
Stoxx 50 Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, dropped
0.4 percent to 2,866.23.  Alstom SA (ALO)   The French power equipment maker began
construction on a 50 million-real ($30 million) wind turbine
factory in  Brazil  to take advantage of the growing renewable
energy market, the Paris-based company said today in an e-mailed
statement. Alstom added 0.1 percent to 41.33 euros.  Banque Nationale de Belgique (BNB)  SA:  Belgium ’s
publicly traded central bank said net income declined to 832
million euros ($1.17 billion) last year and will raise its
ordinary dividend 31 percent to 166.12 euros a share. Banque
Nationale de Belgique climbed 2.2 percent to 3,393 euros.  Deutsche Boerse AG (DB1)  (DB1 GY): The exchange operator that
last month said it will buy NYSE Euronext and create the world’s
largest operator of stock and derivatives exchanges forecast
revenue may rise as much as 10 percent in 2011 if “confidence
in global markets” improves.        Exmar NV (EXM)  : Chief Executive Officer Nicolas Saverys
sold 176,000 of the gas-tanker owner’s shares for an average
6.48 euros apiece in an off-market transaction on March 18,
according to a regulatory filing. Exmar gained 3.9 percent to
6.48 euros.        Korian (KORI)  : The retirement-home operator said 2010
sales advanced 8.5 percent to 923 million euros and net income
jumped 65 percent to 24.7 million euros, and forecast 2011
revenue will climb at least 7 percent. Korian shares climbed 1.5
percent to 16.70 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Jennifer A. Johnson in New York at 
